records.nl_statement: Let $F = \mathbb{Z}_p$ be the field of integers $\mod p$, where $p$ is a prime, and let $q(x) \in F[x]$ be irreducible of degree $n$. Show that $F[x]/(q(x))$ is a field having at exactly $p^n$ elements.

  IsField (Polynomial (ZMod p) ⧸ span {q}) :=

noncomputable def is_topology (X : Type*) (T : Set (Set X)) :=
  univ ∈ T ∧
  (∀ s t, s ∈ T → t ∈ T → s ∩ t ∈ T) ∧
  (∀s, (∀t ∈ s, t ∈ T) → sUnion s ∈ T)
